South African-born Master KG has people around the globe dancing to his hit track 'Jerusalema'. JOHANNESBURG - President Ramaphosa is challenging South Africans this Heritage Day. He is urging South Africans to do the Jerusalema dance challenge. READ: Master KG continues to break barriers with Jerusalema People across the globe have been jiving to Master KG's hit song. Now, the President wants you to do the same to celebrate your heritage. "There can be no better way to celebrate our South Africans than joining the global phenomenon that is spreading across the world, and that is the Jerusalema Dance Challenge. I urge all of you to take up this challenge on Heritage Day," he said. President Cyril Ramaphosa announced that South Africa is moving to Level 1 of the lockdown.